In Montenegro we hung out at The White Rabbit Bar. It had daytime sales people who wanted to sell us sunglasses, and nighttime DJs giving satanic eye-signs. “Montenegro is tall blue mountains,” declares Mike. His head is in a play sandwich. How can he think straight?

The best fortress. “That’s where we stash the old people’s luggage,” says Martin. Scene of a giant 2016 breakout involving Mr Duck who’s climbed the Lexus of goats. Weeded out as an intruder.

Here came the end. Istanbul, actually a convergence point – please recite truth from My Little Pony… “Beauty, bravery, kindness, and honesty. Isn’t that right, Pinkie Pie?” Says Mike.

Thennnnnnnnnn the Weren’t Expecting That Vengeful Bastard Bit.

Well, if we’re giving random insight and back of the bar tidbits, let’s give you some good news Mr Duck. Martin here’s favourite country, Albania, came to a screeching and murky halt. They are stuck in the border which wasn’t meant to have customs as it’s just transitional. But because their system’s being treated like third tier Yugoslavia by the un-psychotic Yugoslavia of the EU, everything
